<title>UK: Post Office invests 100 mln stg, creates 700 jobs.</title>
<headline>Post Office invests 100 mln stg, creates 700 jobs.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The UK Post Office announced on Wednesday plans to build a 100 million stg distribution centre for its Parcelforce business, creating 700 jobs in Coventry.</p>
<p>Kevin Williams, managing director of Parcelforce, said it was the largest investment to date in the division and will create the biggest postal distribution centre in Europe. It is due to open in 1999 and will handle the anticipated 50 percent growth in the express postal market over the coming decade.</p>
